Dear Peter,
The Tennessee House Democratic Caucus wishes you a safe and happy Independence Day! As we celebrate our country’s independence, we honor and acknowledge the sacrifices made by our forefathers. The freedoms and rights we enjoy as Americans are the result of the many sacrifices of those who came before us.
Unfortunately, Tennesseans’ rights are being limited, and our freedoms are under attack by the GOP supermajority in the Tennessee House. That’s why the Tennessee House Democratic Caucus is continuing its fight for freedom for every Tennessean.
Tennesseans should be free to:
-attend sufficiently funded, fully staffed public schools;
-read works of literature in a fully-stocked library;
-vote in a convenient manner;
-make reproductive and other healthcare choices;
-access quality, affordable healthcare;
-breathe clean air, drink clean water and farm clean soil;
-travel on reliable public transit and passenger rail;
-live in safe communities free of gun violence;
-earn a living wage and have access to affordable housing;
-love whomever they wish; and
-live their American dream.
Tennessee House Democrats are fully committed to organizing and working hard to elect strong candidates up and down the ballot who will join our ongoing fight against House Republican extremists who seek to undermine our great country and limit our rights and freedoms.
We firmly believe in the power of unity and collective action to continue our collective fight for Tennessee and our values. Thank you for standing and fighting with us on this Day of Independence.
With sincere appreciation,
Rep. John Ray Clemmons
Chairman, TN House Democratic Caucus
